---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About | Aveen Dayal"
  description="Aveen Dayal's research journey from autonomous systems and domain shift to reliable multimodal and generative AI."
>
  <section class="page-hero section-shell about-hero">
    <div data-reveal>
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>A research journey shaped by systems, shifts, and questions of reliability.</h1>
      <p class="page-lead">
        From autonomous systems and edge AI to multimodal generation, interpretation, attribution, protection, and evaluation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-story section-shell">
    <div class="prose-large" data-reveal>
      <p>
        I am a Senior Multimodal AI Researcher at Dolby Laboratories’ Advanced Technology Group in Bengaluru. My research spans multimodal and generative AI, mechanistic interpretability, content attribution and protection, robust model evaluation, domain generalization and adaptation, and efficient inference. Across these areas, I am interested in a common question: how can we build AI systems whose behaviour remains understandable, dependable, and practically useful outside controlled settings?
      </p>
      <p>
        My research journey began during the final semester of my undergraduate studies, when I joined the Autonomous and Cyber-Physical Systems Lab at the University of Agder in Norway as a visiting researcher. Working across autonomous systems, edge AI, and sensor-driven learning introduced me to the gap between strong laboratory performance and reliable operation in unfamiliar environments. That experience shaped my doctoral research at IIT Hyderabad, where I studied the generalizability and adaptability of deep learning models under domain shift.
      </p>
      <p>
        Alongside my academic work, research experiences at Microsoft Research India and Adobe Research exposed me to large language models, multimodal systems, generative modelling, and efficient inference from complementary perspectives. I now continue this journey at Dolby, working on research problems at the intersection of intelligent media, reliable evaluation, attribution, protection, and deployment.
      </p>
      <p>
        My broader goal is to connect theoretical understanding with practical systems: models that can be examined rather than treated as opaque, evaluated beyond narrow benchmarks, traced and protected when they generate content, and made efficient enough to operate in real-world environments.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="personal-note">
    <div class="section-shell personal-note-inner" data-reveal>
      <p class="eyebrow">A personal note</p>
      <p class="personal-note-copy">
        I am deeply grateful to the mentors who trusted me with opportunities, challenged my assumptions, and helped shape the way I approach research; to the colleagues whose thoughtful conversations continually broadened and sharpened my understanding; and to the friends and family whose encouragement and emotional strength sustained me throughout this journey. I feel extraordinarily fortunate to have learned, grown, and worked alongside them.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="gallery-section section-shell">
    <div class="section-heading" data-reveal>
      <div><p class="eyebrow">Along the way</p><h2>Places, people, and moments</h2></div>
      <p>Gallery images can be added later without changing the layout.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="gallery-grid" data-reveal>
      <div class="gallery-placeholder gallery-large"><span>University of Agder</span></div>
      <div class="gallery-placeholder"><span>IIT Hyderabad</span></div>
      <div class="gallery-placeholder"><span>Research conferences</span></div>
      <div class="gallery-placeholder"><span>Microsoft Research</span></div>
      <div class="gallery-placeholder gallery-wide"><span>Adobe Research · Dolby</span></div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
